Duit (formerly DUI; now GtkD) is a D language graphical user interface wrapping (or binding) GTK+ graphical toolkit

GtkD is released under the LGPL license.

==GtkD Code Example==
 <font color = blue>import</font> gtk.MainWindow;
 <font color = blue>import</font> gtk.Label;
 <font color = blue>import</font> gtk.Main;
 <font color = blue>void</font> main( string[] args )
 {
  Main.init(args);
  MainWindow win = <font color = blue>new</font> MainWindow(<font color = green>"Hello World"</font>);
  win.setDefaultSize(200, 100);
  win.add(<font color = blue>new</font> Label(<font color = green>"Hello World"</font>));
  win.showAll();
  Main.run();   // here was Main.main(), which was wrong
 }


