In [[Cookbook:Cuisine of France|French cuisine]] '''mirepoix''' is a mixture of finely diced vegetables used as a base for stocks, soups and stews. Typically it consists of two parts [[Cookbook:onion|onion]], and one part each of [[Cookbook:celery|celery]] and [[Cookbook:carrot|carrot]] gently fried in [[Cookbook:butter|butter]] or [[Cookbook:Olive Oil|olive oil]] until soft. [[Cookbook:Leek|Leek]]s, [[Cookbook:bacon|bacon]] or [[Cookbook:herb|herb]]s can sometimes be added.

