{{Gothic}} Here is your vocabulary for this chapter. Note that there will be other vocabulary in the Pronouns and Articles sections that will be integrated within the tutorial.: === Nouns === {|class="wikitable" |- !Gothic !Latin !Definition !Gender |- |𐌷𐌿𐌽𐌳𐍃 |Hunds |A Dog/Hound |Masculine |- |𐌱𐌰𐌿𐍂𐌲𐌾𐌰 |Baúrgja |Citizen |Feminine |- |𐍃𐍅𐌴𐌹𐌽 |Swein |Pig |Masculine |- |𐍆𐍉𐌽 |fon |Fire |Neuter |- |}
=== Verbs === {|class="wikitable" |- !Gothic !Latin !Definition !Gender |- |𐌳𐍂𐌴𐌹𐌱𐌰𐌽 |Dreiban |To Drive |Masculine |- |𐌱𐌴𐌹𐍄𐌰𐌽 |Beitan |To Bite |Masculine |- |}
Try to memorize them in the Gothic alphabet based on the Latin transcription. In further lessons when these are used, they will not use destinguished Latin characters and you must be able to know how to truly pronnounce them. When to use which version of the word "the" will be covered in another page within this chapter.

